# Svelte Rules for AI

## Framework
- SvelteKit with adapter-static (SPA mode)
- Svelte 5 with runes ($state, $derived, $effect, $props)
- JavaScript (NOT TypeScript)
- Vite as build tool

## Patterns
- Use `$state()` for reactive state
- Use `$derived()` for computed values (perfect for idle game calculations)
- Use `$effect()` sparingly — prefer onMount/onDestroy for lifecycle
- Use `$props()` for component props
- Use `{@render children()}` for slot content (Svelte 5 syntax)
- Put shared game state in `.svelte.js` files so runes work outside components
- Components go in `src/lib/components/`
- Game logic goes in `src/lib/game/`
- Utility functions go in `src/lib/utils/`

## Style
- Use component-scoped `<style>` blocks (Svelte default)
- Global styles in `src/app.css`
- CSS custom properties (--color-*, --font-*) for theming
- Pixel font: 'Press Start 2P'
- Dark background, glowing accents

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase.svelte (e.g., UpgradeCard.svelte)
- JS modules: camelCase.js (e.g., formatNumber.js)
- Svelte state files: name.svelte.js (so runes work)

## Don'ts
- Do NOT use TypeScript
- Do NOT use SSR (it's disabled in +layout.js)
- Do NOT import from $app/server
- Do NOT use Svelte 4 syntax (no `export let`, no `$$props`, no `<slot>`)
